{"title_page": "Ghost Hawk Brewing Company", "text_new": "{{Infobox brewery\n| name             = Ghost Hawk Brewing Company\n| logo             = [[File:GhostHawkLogo.png]]\n| type             = Microbrewery\n| predecessor      = \n| successor        = \n| foundation       = \n| founder          = \n| defunct          = \n| location_place   = 321 River Road #6\n| location_city    = Clifton\n| location_state   = New Jersey\n| location_country = USA\n| coordinates      = \n| opened           = 2019\n| closed           =\n| area_served      = \n| key_people       = Steven Bauer \n| industry         = \n| production       = 1,200\n| other_products = \n| revenue          = \n| owner            = \n| num_employees    = \n| parent           = \n| divisions        = \n| subsid           = \n| distribution     = On-site\n| tasting          = Tastings and tours on Tuesday-Sunday\n| url              = https://www.ghosthawkbrewing.com/\n| footnotes        = \n| intl             = \n}}\n\n'''Ghost Hawk Brewing Company''' is a [[microbrewery]] in [[Clifton, New Jersey|Clifton]] and is the only production brewery in [[Passaic County, New Jersey|Passaic County]], [[New Jersey]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://newjerseycraftbeer.com/new-jersey-breweries/|title=New Jersey Breweries & Brewpubs|date=February 17, 2020|website=New Jersey Craft Beer}}</ref>\n\n==History==\nGhost Hawk was started by Clifton natives Thomas Rachelski and Steven Bauer, but it grew to encompass Chris Sheehan, who was the head brewer at [[List of breweries in New York#Closed Breweries|Chelsea Craft Brewery]] and \n[[List of breweries in New York#Bronx|Gun Hill Brewing]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mnmagazine.com/2019/03/what-makes-a-beer/|title=What Makes a Beer? \u2013 MN Magazine}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tapinto.net/sections/nj-flavor/articles/ghost-hawk-is-the-first-craft-brewery-in-passaic-county-5724f18c-20a1-4b85-950f-acc856bd1012|title=Ghost Hawk is the First Craft Brewery in Passaic County|website=TAPinto}}</ref> The brewery opened April 20, 2019 and was the first production brewery in Passaic County since [[Paterson Consolidated Brewing Company]] closed after [[Prohibition]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.northjersey.com/story/life/food/2019/04/02/ghost-hawk-brewery-clifton-hold-grand-opening-april-20/3341039002/|title=Ghost Hawk Brewery in Clifton to hold grand opening on April 20|first=Rebecca|last=King|website=North Jersey}}</ref> They came in 2nd place during [[News 12 Networks|News 12]]'s 2019 Brewery Battle.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://longisland.news12.com/story/40820207/brewery-battle-2019|title=Closing time for News 12\u2019s Brewery Battle|website=longisland.news12.com}}</ref> In December 2019 the brewery almost shut down when one of the founders suffered from a stroke, but a GoFund me was created and raised $15,000.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://dailyvoice.com/new-jersey/southpassaic/news/support-pours-in-for-owner-of-passaic-countys-first-craft-brewery-who-suffered-stroke/781762/|title=Support Pours In For Owner Of Passaic County's First Craft Brewery Who Suffered Stroke|date=January 12, 2020|website=South Passaic Daily Voice}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.northjersey.com/story/food/beer/2020/02/05/ghost-hawk-brewing-co-owner-designs-new-release-after-surviving-stroke/4658963002/|title=Bauer is back: Ghost Hawk Brewing Co. owner designs 'Cerebral Artery' can after surviving stroke|first=Rebecca|last=King|website=North Jersey}}</ref> Currently they produce about 1,200 barrels a year in their 15-barrel brewhouse and is on tap in over 100 different bars and restaurants in norther and central New Jersey.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ghosthawkbrewing.com/find-us|title=Ghost Hawk Brewing Co \u2014 Find Us|website=Ghost Hawk Brewing Co}}</ref>\n\n==Beers and other products==\nGhost Hawk brews many different beers, but has four Flagship products:\n*Ghost Hawk [[Lager]]\n*Apex Predator [[India pale ale#United States|New England IPA]]\n*Ravendark [[Stout#Dry or Irish stout|Foreign Export Stout]]\n*[[Daedalion]] [[Wheat Beer]]\n\n==Licensing and associations==\nGhost Hawk has a [[Beer in New Jersey#Brewery licenses and regulation|limited brewery license]] from the [[New Jersey Division of Alcoholic Beverage Control]], which allows it to produce up to 300,000 barrels of beer per year, to sell on-premises as part of a tour, and to distribute to wholesalers and at festivals.The brewery is a member of the New Jersey Brewers Association<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.courierpostonline.com/story/life/2020/02/04/nj-breweries-100-plus-women-come-together-make-beer-womens-brew-day-cherry-hill/4648977002/|title=NJ Breweries: 100-plus women come together to make beer on Women's Brew Day in Cherry Hill|first=Tammy|last=Paolino|website=Courier-Post}}</ref><ref>Garden State Craft Brewers Guild. [http://www.njbeer.org/members/ \"The Garden State Craft Brewer's Guild: Our Members.\"] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130325073237/http://www.njbeer.org/members/ |date=March 25, 2013 }} Retrieved 8 October 2013.</ref> and New Jersey Craft Beer Club.<ref>New Jersey Craft Beer Club. [http://newjerseycraftbeer.com/new-jersey-breweries/ \"New Jersey Breweries and BrewPubs\"] Retrieved 25 November 2013.</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Alcohol laws of New Jersey]]\n*[[Beer in New Jersey]]\n*[[List of wineries, breweries, and distilleries in New Jersey]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{New Jersey Wineries, Breweries, and Distilleries}}\n\n[[:Category:Beer brewing companies based in New Jersey]]\n[[:Category:2019 establishments in New Jersey]]\n[[:Category:Clifton, New Jersey]]\n[[:Category:Beer brewing companies based in Passaic County, New Jersey]]\n\n{{Uncategorized|date=May 2020}}\n", "text_old": "\n\n{{Infobox brewery\n| name             = Ghost Hawk Brewing Company\n| logo             = [[File:GhostHawkLogo.png]]\n| type             = Microbrewery\n| predecessor      = \n| successor        = \n| foundation       = 